gomodel:SYNGO_1057  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: IQ-ArfGEF/BRAG1/IQSEC2 is a guanine nucleotide exchange factor present in postsynaptic densities of glutamatergic synapses.\n\nOverexpression of wildtype BRAG1 in CA1 pyramidal cells in rat hippocampal organotypic slice cultures causes an increase in AMPA receptor mediated responses (Fig.1c, d).\n\nOverexpression of a dominant-negative mutant BRAG1-E849K, which lacks Arf-GEF enzymatic activity, still causes an increase in AMPA receptor mediated responses (Fig. 1b), indicating that the enhancement in AMPA receptor responses is unrelated to the enzymatic activity of BRAG1, but rather depends on its C-terminal interactions with PSD-95 (Fig.2).\n\nKnock-down (KD) of BRAG1 using different siRNA constructs causes a reduction in AMPA receptor mediated responses (Fig.7a-e) that can be rescued by expression of wildtype BRAG1 (Fig.7f). BRAG1 overexpression increases surface expression levels of GluA2 (Fig. 6), but overexpression or KD of BRAG1 has no effect on LTP generation at the CA3-CA1 SC synapse (Fig.9). However, KD of BRAG1 affects LTD indicating that removal of AMPA receptors is affected in the absence of BRAG1 and this effect depends on the enzymatic Arf-GEF activity of BRAG1 (Fig.10).\n\nIn summary, these data indicate that BRAG1 modulates the expression levels of AMPA receptors at postsynapses.. Experimental description: FLAG-tagged human wild-type BRAG1 (BRAG1) and BRAG1-E849K in the pCAGGS vector were generated as described previously.\n\n3/7/2017 Pim\nCombination of rat neurons + shRNA are used with rescues of human overexpressed protein. I annotated against human sequence because no reviewed sequence for IQSEC2 exists in Uniprot for rat species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1057" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .
